                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-02-02</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>So far I've read the first 30 pages, covering 1 1/2 of his thinking tools. What I've learned is: don't be a stubborn person, consider alternatives. There are more specifics like consider the positive aspects of a position, the negative aspects, and the interesting aspects, but it all boils down to considering alternatives. I'll let you guys know if there is any more to the book when I finish it.</span>
                  
              
